{"name":"Multifocal Barrage","type":"technique","img":"/systems/tyoa/assets/default/art.png","system":{"lvl":"2","pattern":"white","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"description":"<p id=\"docs-internal-guid-53d3ea14-7fff-572a-43e8-67af35941d1a\" dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Ubuntu,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">(Spell, Metamancy 2, Any Magic Skill 2):</span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Ubuntu,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">You are proficient in multiple types of magic, and your understanding of the ways that magical energies intertwine have allowed you to combine your proficiencies into one. By committing Effort for the week as a spell, you may combine your magical energies into a single, devastating effect. Roll a ranged attack, using your Metamancy skill level. On a hit, you deal 1d8 worth of damage for each magical skill, including Metamancy, which you have trained to level 2 or higher. </span></p>","save":"","skill":"Metamancy","magic":true,"effort":0,"time":"Week","range":""},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"tyoa","systemVersion":"0.1.0","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1675298271072,"modifiedTime":1675987932531,"lastModifiedBy":"vtQVXu8um2tryua5"},"_id":"56SPKaxhzwN7gruV","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"vtQVXu8um2tryua5":3}}
{"name":"Power Knows Power","type":"technique","img":"/systems/tyoa/assets/default/art.png","system":{"lvl":"1","pattern":"white","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"description":"<p id=\"docs-internal-guid-b3be542e-7fff-6930-6733-4eea7e434c10\" dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Ubuntu,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">(Art, Metamancy 1):</span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Ubuntu,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">You are acquainted with the power of magic, and have seen it reflected in all others who wield the same power. By casually observing or interacting with a target, you may recognize other mages, magical beings, and even gods for what they are, so long as they are not explicitly trying to hide their nature. If they are trying to hide, you may reach out to them magically and make an opposed Metamancy skill check to determine their nature. This more intrusive act, however, will never go unnoticed by the target.</span></p>","save":"","skill":"Metamancy","magic":false,"effort":0,"time":"","range":""},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"tyoa","systemVersion":"0.1.0","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1675298271072,"modifiedTime":1675987932484,"lastModifiedBy":"vtQVXu8um2tryua5"},"_id":"82rCvkBjzlNC2Rfb","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"vtQVXu8um2tryua5":3}}
{"name":"Magic Cauldron","type":"technique","img":"/systems/tyoa/assets/default/art.png","system":{"lvl":"3","pattern":"white","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"description":"<p id=\"docs-internal-guid-e4cf4b80-7fff-f9df-94d5-efb5616919ef\" dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Ubuntu,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">(Special, Metamancy 3, Crafting 1):</span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Ubuntu,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">You are able to use a special cauldron imbued with your magic energies while brewing concoctions, and you may add your Metamancy skill level to skill checks made with the cauldron. Additionally, beneficial potions and elixirs restore an additional 1d4 HP when being consumed and harmful concoctions deal an additional 1d4 damage when being applied.</span></p>","save":"","skill":"Metamancy","magic":false,"effort":0,"time":"","range":""},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"tyoa","systemVersion":"0.1.0","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1675298271072,"modifiedTime":1675987932581,"lastModifiedBy":"vtQVXu8um2tryua5"},"_id":"Cr0lBhSkLmJv2nnj","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"vtQVXu8um2tryua5":3}}
{"name":"Well-Practiced Mage","type":"technique","img":"/systems/tyoa/assets/default/art.png","system":{"lvl":"0","pattern":"white","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"description":"<p id=\"docs-internal-guid-b5fa8391-7fff-1490-6694-75d437382a7a\" dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Ubuntu,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Well-Practiced Mage</span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Ubuntu,sans-serif; color: #1155cc; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">*</span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Ubuntu,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"> (Art, Metamancy 0):</span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Ubuntu,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Ubuntu,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">You&rsquo;ve put in long hours honing your mind to perform magic. As a result, your total Effort increases by 1. </span></p>","save":"","skill":"Metamancy","magic":false,"effort":0,"time":"","range":""},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"tyoa","systemVersion":"0.1.0","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1675299078167,"modifiedTime":1675987932468,"lastModifiedBy":"vtQVXu8um2tryua5"},"_id":"FIkuUgZ2UjXBzrnx","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"vtQVXu8um2tryua5":3}}
{"name":"Identify Magic","type":"technique","img":"/systems/tyoa/assets/default/art.png","system":{"lvl":"1","pattern":"white","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"description":"<p id=\"docs-internal-guid-7802ab7f-7fff-7ddb-ba93-0206a368e7b7\" dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Ubuntu,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">(Ritual, Metamancy 1):</span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Ubuntu,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">You may spend a scene examining any magical items, structures, or standing magical effects to determine their purpose. You gain a full description of all unhidden magical effects present, and may roll a Metamancy skill check to discover hidden or cursed magical features. If the hidden effect is related to another school of magic, you may alternatively use that skill in place of Metamancy for this skill check.</span></p>","save":"","skill":"Metamancy","magic":false,"effort":0,"time":"","range":""},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"tyoa","systemVersion":"0.1.0","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1675298271072,"modifiedTime":1675987932478,"lastModifiedBy":"vtQVXu8um2tryua5"},"_id":"FxDiqyB2lY6exfTL","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"vtQVXu8um2tryua5":3}}
{"name":"Metamancy Core Technique","type":"technique","img":"/systems/tyoa/assets/default/art.png","system":{"lvl":"0","pattern":"white","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"description":"<p id=\"docs-internal-guid-1ec9a513-7fff-82f9-cc49-452f2a4bf5e7\" dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Ubuntu,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">(Spell):</span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Ubuntu,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"> </span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Ubuntu,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">By taking any training in this skill, you gain access to magic. You have a minimum Effort of 1, which increases as described above. You gain the ability to identify any magic performed in your presence as magical, unless it is specifically concealed. You may identify any magical items or structures as magical, although you do not receive specific information about their purpose. You may perform freeform rituals related to Metamancy, as described on page {{PAGE}}.&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-indent: 36pt; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Ubuntu,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">At level 1, as a spell, you may channel your raw magical energy into a ranged attack that deals d4 + Metamancy skill damage if it hits. The range of this attack is 30ft + 10ft per Metamancy level. This attack may use Metamancy in place of Marksmanship when making attack rolls.</span></p>\n<p id=\"docs-internal-guid-704f9ef7-7fff-232e-0a3c-259bb445db93\" dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Ubuntu,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">&nbsp;</span></p>","save":"","skill":"Metamancy","magic":false,"effort":0,"time":"","range":""},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"tyoa","systemVersion":"0.1.0","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1675298271072,"modifiedTime":1675987932470,"lastModifiedBy":"vtQVXu8um2tryua5"},"_id":"G5HiQ7p9rVl1TcJn","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"vtQVXu8um2tryua5":3}}
{"name":"Spellbook","type":"technique","img":"/systems/tyoa/assets/default/art.png","system":{"lvl":"0","pattern":"white","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"description":"<p id=\"docs-internal-guid-f83eb08a-7fff-c72e-b440-7e75e6e8764e\" dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Ubuntu,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">(Special, Metamancy 0, Knowledge 0):</span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Ubuntu,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"> </span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Ubuntu,sans-serif; color: #ff0000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Incompatible with Psion.</span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Ubuntu,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">You have taken a more academic approach to learning magic. Instead of learning techniques the traditional way through practice, you instead learn just enough about them to record them in your personal grimoire or spellbook. Learning techniques this way takes time, but does not cost any skill points. Recording a technique into your grimoire requires you to find a tutor who knows the spell, or another mage&rsquo;s grimoire to work off of, and must be performed as a year action. You do not need to be trained in the skill of the technique you are acquiring, instead using your Metamancy skill level in place of the minimum magic skill level of the technique. If a technique has another prerequisite technique, you must record that technique in your grimoire first, and it may be assumed that you are using all necessary knowledge to cast from your grimoire. There is no limit to the number of spells you may record. Once recorded, you may cast any technique from your grimoire as a Ritual, committing Effort as normally required by the technique. Casting techniques this way always requires a minimum of one Effort to be committed for the week. Arts that are normally learned as permanent effects will instead last no longer than a week when cast this way. A grimoire has an encumbrance value of 1.</span></p>","save":"","skill":"Metamancy","magic":true,"effort":0,"time":"Week","range":""},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"tyoa","systemVersion":"0.1.0","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1675299078167,"modifiedTime":1675987932477,"lastModifiedBy":"vtQVXu8um2tryua5"},"_id":"GkDiSBQXUQOIcAAC","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"vtQVXu8um2tryua5":3}}
{"name":"Second Nature","type":"technique","img":"/systems/tyoa/assets/default/art.png","system":{"lvl":"2","pattern":"white","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"description":"<p id=\"docs-internal-guid-c8843e71-7fff-b100-80ad-7fde9e85943b\" dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Ubuntu,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">(Art, Metamancy 2): </span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Ubuntu,sans-serif; color: #1155cc; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Requires Well-Practiced Mage.</span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Ubuntu,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Ubuntu,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">You are so attuned to casting magic that it has become second nature to you. Your Effort increases by 1.</span></p>","save":"","skill":"Metamancy","magic":false,"effort":0,"time":"","range":""},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"tyoa","systemVersion":"0.1.0","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1675298271072,"modifiedTime":1675987932572,"lastModifiedBy":"vtQVXu8um2tryua5"},"_id":"I930BJPP5Tsqsp64","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"vtQVXu8um2tryua5":3}}
{"name":"Magitechnician","type":"technique","img":"/systems/tyoa/assets/default/art.png","system":{"lvl":"0","pattern":"white","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"description":"<p id=\"docs-internal-guid-d2110c7b-7fff-2939-5f4c-51f2706b195a\" dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Ubuntu,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">(Art, Metamancy 0, Crafting 1): </span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Ubuntu,sans-serif; color: #1155cc; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Requires Enchanter.</span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Ubuntu,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">In addition to magic, you are highly skilled in the art of crafting, and know the inner weavings and workings of items you seek to enchant. When rolling Enchanter skill checks, you may add half of your Crafting skill level, rounded up to the result.</span></p>\n<p id=\"docs-internal-guid-704f9ef7-7fff-232e-0a3c-259bb445db93\" dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Ubuntu,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">&nbsp;</span></p>","save":"","skill":"Metamancy","magic":false,"effort":0,"time":"","range":""},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"tyoa","systemVersion":"0.1.0","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1675298271072,"modifiedTime":1675987932473,"lastModifiedBy":"vtQVXu8um2tryua5"},"_id":"NCUqD0AM7P9HZ0V1","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"vtQVXu8um2tryua5":3}}
{"name":"Create Wand","type":"technique","img":"/systems/tyoa/assets/default/art.png","system":{"lvl":"3","pattern":"white","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"description":"<p id=\"docs-internal-guid-f4c56d90-7fff-5de7-eb55-b13a184407ca\" dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Ubuntu,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">(Ritual, Metamancy 3, Crafting 1): </span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Ubuntu,sans-serif; color: #1155cc; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Requires Enchanter.</span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Ubuntu,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Wands are powerful and rare tools, used by certain mages who have access to the materials necessary to create one. A skilled enchanter who is also able to craft powerful objects using their hands may attempt to create the perfect balance in a wand that will accept and hold magic. This process takes a week of time, and material costs equivalent to the intended power of the magic that it will hold. A wand for level 0 spells and arts costs 1,000sp in material costs, level 1 costs 2,000sp, level 2 costs 4,000sp, level 3 costs 8,000sp, level 4 costs 16,000sp, and level 5 costs 32,000sp. These material components are lost in a failed attempt. At the end of the week, the enchanter rolls a difficulty 12 skill check, adding both their Metamancy and Crafting skill levels. If they successfully create a wand, it can be bound to a caster, allowing them to cast any single Spell or Art at or below the wand&rsquo;s level into the wand at its normal Effort or Stress cost. This technique is stored indefinitely, and can be unleashed at any time by the owner as a spell without expending Effort. A character may only own and operate one wand at a time.</span></p>","save":"","skill":"Metamancy","magic":false,"effort":0,"time":"","range":""},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"tyoa","systemVersion":"0.1.0","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1675298271072,"modifiedTime":1675987932579,"lastModifiedBy":"vtQVXu8um2tryua5"},"_id":"SpW7r0xb6YQuqYxC","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"vtQVXu8um2tryua5":3}}
{"name":"Enchanter","type":"technique","img":"/systems/tyoa/assets/default/art.png","system":{"lvl":"2","pattern":"white","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"description":"<p id=\"docs-internal-guid-bf914659-7fff-fe84-d967-3e50febc89d8\" dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Ubuntu,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">(Special, Metamancy 2):</span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Ubuntu,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"> </span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Ubuntu,sans-serif; color: #85200c; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">May not be recorded as a spellbook technique.</span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Ubuntu,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"> Some very talented spellweavers may channel their power into inanimate objects, enchanting them with all manner of magical abilities, effects, and enhancements. Magical items might range from simple abilities to incredibly detailed and unique items. Magical items are limited only by the enchanter&rsquo;s imagination, provided you have the necessary materials and skill. Generally, enchantment requires at least 10x the base price of the item you are enchanting in magical materials, and the item need not be a weapon or piece of armor. An enchantment should cost at least 500sp, even for simple item enchantments. The enchanter must spend around one week per significant enchantment or feature added, and then roll a difficulty 10 Metamancy skill check in order to successfully enchant the item. Alternatively, if the enchantment directly relates to another magical skill that a character has, they may use that skill in place of Metamancy. Failure does not damage the item, but does consume the material cost of the enchantment. Items with modifications on them may be enchanted at no additional difficulty. At the discretion of a GM, items may be enchanted multiple times, although the difficulty or cost may increase with each additional enchantment.</span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-indent: 36pt; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Ubuntu,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Magic items are very open ended in The Years of Adventure, designed to support existing content, ease of use for game masters, and most importantly, the creative ideas of players. When presented with particularly outlandish ideas from players, GMs are encouraged to experiment with these rules. The GM may decide that the items are being enchanted with highly powerful effects, in which case additional material cost or a more difficult skill check may be called for. Generally speaking, magic items that provide flat bonuses to skills and attacks or damage, or provide access to arts and techniques should either be discouraged or very expensive. Specifically, enchantments that provide simple statistic bonuses like increased attack, damage, and armor class, or decreased encumbrance, are more appropriately handled as Modifications, and not magical enchantments. A sample of example magical items may be found in the Appendix.</span></p>","save":"","skill":"Metamancy","magic":false,"effort":0,"time":"","range":""},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"tyoa","systemVersion":"0.1.0","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1675298271072,"modifiedTime":1675987932521,"lastModifiedBy":"vtQVXu8um2tryua5"},"_id":"WTOlFxRO8sXAMdeh","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"vtQVXu8um2tryua5":3}}
{"name":"Battle Caster","type":"technique","img":"/systems/tyoa/assets/default/art.png","system":{"lvl":"3","pattern":"white","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"description":"<p id=\"docs-internal-guid-7ce6b09c-7fff-70a7-70ce-c2416329cb5c\" dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Ubuntu,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">(Art, Metamancy 3, Toughness 3):</span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Ubuntu,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Ubuntu,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">You are able to withstand more pain than your average magic user, allowing you to cast spells even during rounds where you&rsquo;ve taken damage. Ritual spells are still interrupted through damage or magical means.</span></p>","save":"","skill":"Metamancy","magic":false,"effort":0,"time":"","range":""},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"tyoa","systemVersion":"0.1.0","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1675298271072,"modifiedTime":1675987932577,"lastModifiedBy":"vtQVXu8um2tryua5"},"_id":"YLr1pV5vrX1QMi0y","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"vtQVXu8um2tryua5":3}}
{"name":"Minor Magic","type":"technique","img":"/systems/tyoa/assets/default/art.png","system":{"lvl":"0","pattern":"white","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"description":"<p id=\"docs-internal-guid-065097c1-7fff-d942-e6b7-bbd518c5e22a\" dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Ubuntu,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">(Art, Metamancy 0):</span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Ubuntu,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">You may create minor marvels of magic, things that may have impact on the world around them, but are by no means powerful. This might be a candle&rsquo;s worth of light, a tiny illusion, or the whistling of a bird. You could also enchant a broom to sweep by itself, or a harp to pluck its own strings. This art cannot damage or negatively impact a character directly, but can be used intelligently to problem solve or influence situations. A Metamancer may only have one Minor Magic effect at a time, and may begin or cancel an effect as an Instant Action.</span></p>\n<p id=\"docs-internal-guid-704f9ef7-7fff-232e-0a3c-259bb445db93\" dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Ubuntu,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"> </span></p>","save":"","skill":"Metamancy","magic":false,"effort":0,"time":"","range":""},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"tyoa","systemVersion":"0.1.0","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1675298271072,"modifiedTime":1675987932475,"lastModifiedBy":"vtQVXu8um2tryua5"},"_id":"c5n0WXIo9JJRsGx2","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"vtQVXu8um2tryua5":3}}
{"name":"Magic Fists","type":"technique","img":"/systems/tyoa/assets/default/art.png","system":{"lvl":"1","pattern":"white","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"description":"<p id=\"docs-internal-guid-316cd177-7fff-2825-62e7-f52264942087\" dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Ubuntu,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">(Art, Metamancy 1, Fighting 1):</span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Ubuntu,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Ubuntu,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Your melee attacks count as magical attacks for purposes of overcoming certain armor and damaging certain magical creatures that have this as a requirement. Your unarmed attacks have a minimum damage dice size of d6.</span></p>\n<p id=\"docs-internal-guid-7802ab7f-7fff-7ddb-ba93-0206a368e7b7\" dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Ubuntu,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">&nbsp;</span></p>","save":"","skill":"Metamancy","magic":false,"effort":0,"time":"","range":""},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"tyoa","systemVersion":"0.1.0","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1675298271072,"modifiedTime":1675987932480,"lastModifiedBy":"vtQVXu8um2tryua5"},"_id":"fHBQIGqCNJh9gF30","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"vtQVXu8um2tryua5":3}}
{"name":"Quiet Caster","type":"technique","img":"/systems/tyoa/assets/default/art.png","system":{"lvl":"2","pattern":"white","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"description":"<p id=\"docs-internal-guid-2db771d8-7fff-0f06-e590-a2498ce75b93\" dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Ubuntu,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">(Art, Metamancy 2, Stealth 2):&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Ubuntu,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">You have learned how to cast without making any obvious signs that you are doing so. You are able to silently cast, and enemies will need to first pass an opposed Stealth vs. Observation skill check to determine whether they can react in any way to the spell.</span></p>","save":"","skill":"Metamancy","magic":false,"effort":0,"time":"","range":""},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"tyoa","systemVersion":"0.1.0","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1675298271072,"modifiedTime":1675987932575,"lastModifiedBy":"vtQVXu8um2tryua5"},"_id":"kBhlPjiB1BY8ShZm","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"vtQVXu8um2tryua5":3}}
{"name":"Psion","type":"technique","img":"/systems/tyoa/assets/default/art.png","system":{"lvl":"0","pattern":"white","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"description":"<p id=\"docs-internal-guid-704f9ef7-7fff-232e-0a3c-259bb445db93\" dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Ubuntu,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Psion (Special, Metamancy 0): </span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Ubuntu,sans-serif; color: #cc0000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Incompatible with Spellbook.</span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Ubuntu,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">This technique may only be taken if you have no training in magic beyond the Metamancy core technique. Your magical powers are derived entirely from your mind. Rather than learning magical techniques the traditional way, you unlock them through expanding the powers of your mind. You cannot train magical skills aside from Metamancy, and you may not perform Rituals, even those in Metamancy. In return, you may learn Art or Spell techniques (spending skill points as usual) in any magical skill, always using Metamancy in place of the specific magical skill of the technique. If you would like to learn the core technique of a magical skill, you must acquire it at each level, for 1 point at level 0, 2 at level 1, and so forth, but you need not acquire the core technique to learn other techniques in that skill. You may learn Ritual techniques if there is a later technique that allows you to perform it as an Art or Spell, but you may never perform it as a Ritual.</span></p>","save":"","skill":"Metamancy","magic":false,"effort":0,"time":"","range":""},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"tyoa","systemVersion":"0.1.0","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1675298271072,"modifiedTime":1675987932465,"lastModifiedBy":"vtQVXu8um2tryua5"},"_id":"mUmdqtz4ki0QVph9","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"vtQVXu8um2tryua5":3}}
{"name":"Magical Missiles","type":"technique","img":"/systems/tyoa/assets/default/art.png","system":{"lvl":"1","pattern":"white","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"description":"<p id=\"docs-internal-guid-c1c8fdca-7fff-c594-ba75-8dbd081efdf2\" dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Ubuntu,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">(Art, Metamancy 1, Marksmanship 1):</span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Ubuntu,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">You may channel your magical essence into the ammunition you fire. By committing effort for the week, when making a ranged attack with a weapon, you may add a number of d4s equal to your Metamancy skill level to the damage done.</span></p>\n<p id=\"docs-internal-guid-316cd177-7fff-2825-62e7-f52264942087\" dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Ubuntu,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">&nbsp;</span></p>","save":"","skill":"Metamancy","magic":true,"effort":0,"time":"Week","range":""},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"tyoa","systemVersion":"0.1.0","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1675298271072,"modifiedTime":1675987932481,"lastModifiedBy":"vtQVXu8um2tryua5"},"_id":"sEdZbPkm7Ew17qRk","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"vtQVXu8um2tryua5":3}}
{"name":"Proficient Identification","type":"technique","img":"/systems/tyoa/assets/default/art.png","system":{"lvl":"2","pattern":"white","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"description":"<p id=\"docs-internal-guid-fbf8ffb7-7fff-ea2f-cdc3-b5eae5295924\" dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Ubuntu,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">(Spell, Metamancy 2):</span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Ubuntu,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"> </span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Ubuntu,sans-serif; color: #1155cc; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Requires Identify Magic.</span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Ubuntu,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">You may identify magical items and effects as a Main Action, although you must commit Effort for the scene to do so. You may cast this spell retroactively to decipher the effect of a Ritual or Spell cast by someone else since your last turn.</span></p>","save":"","skill":"Metamancy","magic":true,"effort":0,"time":"Scene","range":""},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"tyoa","systemVersion":"0.1.0","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1675298271072,"modifiedTime":1675987932544,"lastModifiedBy":"vtQVXu8um2tryua5"},"_id":"vjB8aGklrW2qOGfW","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"vtQVXu8um2tryua5":3}}
{"name":"Spellbook Memorization","type":"technique","img":"/systems/tyoa/assets/default/art.png","system":{"lvl":"2","pattern":"white","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"description":"<p id=\"docs-internal-guid-2ded0c13-7fff-0517-b451-a2a10d935024\" dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Ubuntu,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">(Special, Metamancy 2):</span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Ubuntu,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"> </span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Ubuntu,sans-serif; color: #1155cc; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Requires Spellbook.&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Ubuntu,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">You are proficient in the use of your spellbook and may cast spells from it more easily. Every week, you may memorize a number of magical techniques equal to twice your Metamancy skill level that are normally cast as an Art or Spell from your spellbook. These memorized techniques may then be cast as a Spell (they may not be cast as an Art) by committing effort for the week. Arts that are normally learned as permanent effects will instead last no longer than a scene when cast this way.</span></p>","save":"","skill":"Metamancy","magic":true,"effort":0,"time":"Week","range":""},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"tyoa","systemVersion":"0.1.0","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1675298271072,"modifiedTime":1675987932549,"lastModifiedBy":"vtQVXu8um2tryua5"},"_id":"wcUhCniU92AmuQI8","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"vtQVXu8um2tryua5":3}}
{"name":"Magically Infused Mundane","type":"technique","img":"/systems/tyoa/assets/default/art.png","system":{"lvl":"5","pattern":"white","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"description":"<p id=\"docs-internal-guid-46b7180c-7fff-622f-f763-b846c49a44f2\" dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Ubuntu,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">(Art, Metamancy 5, Any Mundane Level 5 Skill):</span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Ubuntu,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Someone who has mastered both magic and the mundane can learn to weave the two together, unlocking incredible and unpredictable results. When taking this technique, choose another mundane skill you have level 5 in. From that moment onwards, that skill is infused with magic and receives +1 to skill checks and bonuses at all times. Additionally, you may commit Effort for the week to add your Metamancy skill level to skill checks and bonuses related to a single action. For example, one could add their Metamancy skill level to a single attack and damage roll using Fighting, or could add it to a Stealth or Communication Skill check.</span></p>","save":"","skill":"Metamancy","magic":false,"effort":0,"time":"","range":""},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"tyoa","systemVersion":"0.1.0","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1675298271072,"modifiedTime":1675987932583,"lastModifiedBy":"vtQVXu8um2tryua5"},"_id":"ykznO1mNdIKCktRT","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"vtQVXu8um2tryua5":3}}
